Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.22,0:42:09.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,连续运算20天 用了34 3万处理器时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}running continuously for 28 days, utilizing 343,000 processor-hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.27,0:42:12.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中一项成果是引人注目的3D飞行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One result is a remarkable 3-D fly-through
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.44,0:42:15.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跨越240光年的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across 2.4 billion light-years of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.90,0:42:18.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,演示了数亿个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}showing hundreds of millions of galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.53,0:42:22.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沿着无数股暗物质团聚成星团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}clumped together in clusters along vast strands of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.91,0:42:30.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,利用超级计算机 科学家不仅能研究过去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using supercomputers, scientists not only study the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.96,0:42:34.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且还能预测宇宙的未来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they can predict the future of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.80,0:42:36.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为真是酷毙了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think it's amazingly cool that 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.13,0:42:40.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们实际上能够用上我们所知的宇宙当今的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can actually take what we know about the present-day conditions in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.18,0:42:42.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们基本上能够利用这些计算机模拟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we can basically use these computer simulations
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.51,0:42:44.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来演示时间的推进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to play time forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.31,0:42:48.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够利用这个来推断最终发生在我们身上的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can use this to extrapolate what's going to happen to us in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.85,0:42:54.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个模拟开始于大爆炸留下的量子泡沫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This simulation starts with the quantum foam left over from the Big Bang
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.90,0:42:57.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们穿梭130亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and flies us through 13 billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.99,0:43:02.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伴随它沿着网状的脉络和空隙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it all condenses into the galaxy clusters and superclusters
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.32,0:43:04.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个凝结成星系团和超星系团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}along the network of filaments and voids
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.87,0:43:06.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像那些我们今天所能发现的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like those we can detect today.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.96,0:43:12.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是宇宙团聚现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the cosmic clustering phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.13,0:43:15.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有引力驱动到最大极限\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}driven by gravity to its greatest extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.80,0:43:21.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是引力的牵引被神秘的暗能量给抵消了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But gravity's pull is counterbalanced by the mysterious dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.39,0:43:25.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它正在把宇宙间的星系团驱散\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is driving the galaxy clusters of the universe apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.47,0:43:29.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约10年前 天文学家发现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About a decade ago, astronomers discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.44,0:43:31.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙不光在膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the universe is not just expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.81,0:43:35.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 膨胀正愈演愈快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, its expansion is accelerating with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.03,0:43:41.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力将星系团结合在一块只是在局部层面上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity will keep galaxy clusters together only on a local level.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.86,0:43:46.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的本星系群将会合并为一个超星系团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our local galaxy group will coalesce into one supergalaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.04,0:43:51.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是宇宙间其他所有的星系将会快速远离我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but all other galaxies in the universe will race away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.54,0:43:53.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从今1000亿年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A hundred billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.71,0:43:58.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个宇宙角落将暗无天日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this corner of space will be left virtually in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.22,0:44:03.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们周围的遥远星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As soon as the distant galaxies around us
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.51,0:44:07.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将渐行渐远 达到光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will expand away and reach the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.18,0:44:12.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至它们发出的光线一点都永远无法到达我们这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even light from them will never be able to reach us anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.35,0:44:14.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此这些星系将扩展成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so these galaxies will expand
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.40,0:44:18.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,茫茫空域 并从视野中消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into vast regions of space and disappear from view.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.73,0:44:25.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的星系将成为黑夜中的孤岛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our galaxy will be an island embedded in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.79,0:44:32.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气体云将继续在附近形成星团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Clouds of gas will continue to form into star clusters nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.83,0:44:36.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是未来的天文学家将在我们星系的边界外的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but astronomers of the future will see nothing in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.13,0:44:38.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天空中看不到任何东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}beyond the borders of our own galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.25,0:44:43.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除非今天的宇宙学家的工作得以保存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unless the work of today's cosmologists is preserved,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.09,0:44:45.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,否则将没有任何线索去告诉他们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there will be no clues to tell them
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.43,0:44:49.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曾经有过一次大爆炸 有过宇宙膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there was once a Big Bang and a cosmic expansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.97,0:44:53.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将没有什么能让他们知道广阔天地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}nothing to let them know of the vast existence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.10,0:44:58.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远不止这个空间 就是我们今天所谓的 - 宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}beyond the place we know today as The Universe.
